  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-6">
          End Back-to-Back Meeting Burnout
        </h2>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            Buffer time creates breathing room between meetings automatically.
            Set how much time you need before and after appointments, and
            CalendHub blocks those periods in your calendar. When someone tries
            to book a meeting, the system only shows times that include your
            required buffer. This prevents back-to-back scheduling that leads to
            fatigue, poor preparation, and rushed transitions between important
            conversations.
          </p>

          <p>
            Before meetings, buffer time gives you space to review materials,
            check previous notes, and mentally prepare for the conversation
            ahead. After meetings, buffer time lets you document decisions, send
            follow-up messages, and process what happened before rushing to the
            next appointment. This simple gap between meetings dramatically
            improves meeting quality because you arrive prepared and leave with
            clear next steps instead of constantly playing catch-up.
          </p>

          <p>
            The buffer applies automatically to all new bookings. You configure
            it once per meeting type, and every appointment booked through that
            link includes the specified buffer. A 30-minute meeting with
            15-minute buffers actually blocks 60 minutes in your calendar - 15
            minutes before, 30 minutes for the meeting, and 15 minutes after.
            The booking page only shows available times that accommodate the
            full duration including buffers.
          </p>

          <p>
            Different meeting types benefit from different buffer durations.
            Quick 15-minute check-ins might need only 5-minute buffers for basic
            transitions. Important client presentations or interviews might need
            30-minute buffers for thorough preparation and detailed note-taking.
            CalendHub lets you set appropriate buffer times for each appointment
            type, ensuring the right amount of breathing room for each situation
            without over-blocking your entire calendar.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

